# Cognilot AI Engineering Rules

## 1. Architecture & Tech Stack
- **Monorepo/Structure**: Monorepo using `pnpm workspaces`. Packages:
  - `@cognilot/api`: Hono + Drizzle ORM + Supabase PostgreSQL (Vercel Serverless).
  - `@cognilot/web`: Next.js 15 App Router & Vite Hybrid. Next.js App Router code is in `src/app/` (SSR marketing & CSR dashboard routes). Vite React app views are in `src/views/`.
  - `@cognilot/sdk`: TypeScript ESM core suggestion and detection engines.
  - `@cognilot/extension`: Chrome Extension (Vite + CRXJS).
- **Frontend**: Next.js 15 (App Router) + React 19. State management using standard React hooks and context.
- **Backend**: Hono serverless backend, Drizzle ORM, PostgreSQL database hosted on Supabase. JWT verification signed by Supabase.

## 2. Coding Standards
- **TypeScript**: Strict mode enabled. Avoid the `any` type whenever possible. All core business types must have explicit interfaces or types.
- **ESLint & Prettier**: Configured monorepo-wide with ESLint 9 (due to Next.js 15 peer dependency constraints). Strict rules (like `no-explicit-any`, `only-export-components`, and `set-state-in-effect`) are downgraded to `warn` to allow clean builds and compatibility with Next.js/Vite hybrid routing.
- **Imports**: Avoid absolute paths and file URLs in source code. Use relative imports or `@/` path mapping configured in `tsconfig.json` for frontend projects.

## 3. UI/UX & Design System
- **Aesthetic**: All web views and extension popups/sidebars follow the Terminal/IDE design system:
  - Base background color: `#050505` (dark mode default).
  - Fonts: Monospaced typography (`font-mono`).
  - Elements: Code editor simulator elements (macOS-style points on headers, `//` metadata prefixes, border-bottom inputs, `.sh` style buttons).
- **Styling**: Vanilla CSS and TailwindCSS v4 with modern CSS configuration. Avoid traditional dashboard UI layouts.

## 4. Testing & Workflow
- **Testing**: Using `Vitest` across all packages. Mocking external services and the Chrome Extension API (where applicable) to keep tests fast and deterministic.
- **Pre-commit Hooks**: Husky and lint-staged are configured at the root to run Prettier formatting and lint checks on staged files before commit.
- **Commit Conventions**: Conventional commits format: `type(scope): description` (e.g., `feat(web): add alias editor component`).
